# Site-local firewall allowlist.
# Copy this to 'allowlist.local' (gitignored) and add hosts/IPs your environment
# needs that shouldn't be in the public repo. One entry per line.
#   - hostnames are resolved at firewall init   (e.g. teamcity.corp.example.com)
#   - raw IPv4 and CIDRs are allowed directly    (e.g. 10.20.30.40  or  10.20.0.0/16)
#   - '#' comments and blank lines are ignored
#
# teamcity.corp.example.com
# 10.20.30.40
# 10.20.0.0/16
# google.com
# api.anthropic.com
# sentry.io
#
# github.com
# api.github.com
# codeload.github.com
# objects.githubusercontent.com
# raw.githubusercontent.com
# 140.82.112.0/20
# 143.55.64.0/20
# 192.30.252.0/22
# 185.199.108.0/22   # raw / objects.githubusercontent.com, pages
#
# # package registries
# registry.npmjs.org
# pypi.org
# files.pythonhosted.org
# static.crates.io
# index.crates.io
# proxy.golang.org
# sum.golang.org
#
# # ubuntu apt
# archive.ubuntu.com
